Package: leanfe
Type: Package
Title: Lean Fixed Effects Regression
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: person("Diego", "Gentile Passaro", email = "diegogentilepassaro@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Lean, fast fixed effects regression using Polars and DuckDB.
    Implements the Frisch-Waugh-Lovell theorem for absorbing fixed effects with support
    for IID, HC1 (robust), and clustered standard errors. Optimized for speed and
    memory efficiency on large datasets (10M+ observations).
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Depends: 
    R (>= 3.6.0)
Imports:
    polars (>= 0.8.0),
    duckdb (>= 0.9.0),
    DBI,
    Matrix,
    MASS
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
RoxygenNote: 7.2.0
URL: https://github.com/diegogentilepassaro/leanfe
BugReports: https://github.com/diegogentilepassaro/leanfe/issues
